Amphion and Zethus were sons of Jupiter and Antiope, and remarkable for their dif- ferent tempers. Amphion was fond of music, and Zethus took delight in tending flocks. But as Zethus was naturally of a rugged disposition, (coinpare Propertius, 111. xv. 20. and Statius, Theb. x. 443‚) and hated the lyre, this produced continual disputes between them, until Amphion at length, for the sake of harmony with his brother, renounced music eutirel .
